Sentencas: Different perovskite-based materials are proposed as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) working at low temperatures (similar to 600 degrees C).
Titulo: Wet-Chemical Synthesis and Physico / Electro-Chemical Performance Characteristics of Novel Perovskite Cathode Materials for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this research work, a set of perovskite cathode materials, such as Sm1-xCexCoO3-delta, Sm1-xCexMnO3-delta, Gd1-xCexCoO3-delta and Gd1-xCexMnO3-delta (x = 0.1-0.2) were prepared for SOFC applications by co-precipitation method with sodium hydroxide solution as the precipitating agent.
Titulo: Wet-Chemical Synthesis and Physico / Electro-Chemical Performance Characteristics of Novel Perovskite Cathode Materials for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The precipitated hydroxides were calcined at 300, 600, 750, 900, and 1100 degrees C/2 hours in the air using a thermolyne furnace.
Titulo: Wet-Chemical Synthesis and Physico / Electro-Chemical Performance Characteristics of Novel Perovskite Cathode Materials for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The calcined powder particles were characterized by XRD, FT-IR, Particle Size, SEM, and EDAX techniques.
Titulo: Wet-Chemical Synthesis and Physico / Electro-Chemical Performance Characteristics of Novel Perovskite Cathode Materials for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: XRD patterns revealed the presence of orthorhombic primitive phases in the samples.
Titulo: Wet-Chemical Synthesis and Physico / Electro-Chemical Performance Characteristics of Novel Perovskite Cathode Materials for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Crystallite sizes of the materials were also determined with XRD method.
Titulo: Wet-Chemical Synthesis and Physico / Electro-Chemical Performance Characteristics of Novel Perovskite Cathode Materials for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The presence of M-O bond was confirmed by FT-IR spectroscopy.
Titulo: Wet-Chemical Synthesis and Physico / Electro-Chemical Performance Characteristics of Novel Perovskite Cathode Materials for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Particle size analysis proved the presence of samples in the range of 247-976 nm.

Sentencas: However, the SEM images revealed the presence of nano-sized particles.
